Doctoral thesis on Physics or Material ScienceObjectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the research work is to acquire the skills and techniques of planning and conducting the research and presenting the scientific results. As a result of the research, an independent study will be completed. This study requires an original argumentative solution, and at least three exploratory articles published in internationally acknowledged journals.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The PhD-studend who completed successfully  the course: - Possesses a variety of research methodics in physics or materials science (both experimental and theoretical), - Is able to apply their knowledge on planning and conducting the research in physics or materials science, - Is able to work in an international working environment, - Is able to formulate research issues related to physics or materials science and is able to find the ways to solve them. - Is able to plan and initiate research and development work, - Is able to assess critically the potential outcame of research / development work in the field of physics or material science, - Dares to doubt in the results achieved so far, is able to re-evaluate, re-formulate and / or expand them, if necessary, - Has the management and teamwork skills, - Is able to take strategic decisions, - Is able to argue and participate in professional discussions in both Estonian and English, both in speech and writing, - Is able to publish his/her original research results in peer-reviewed international scientific journals, - Is able to assess his/her need for additional training.
